item.name: Buffer waits, s⁻¹
item.description: Increments each time that a user thread must wait for a buffer.

item.name: Checkpoint waits
item.description: The number of checkpoint waits.

item.name: ISAM commit, s⁻¹
item.description: ISAM. Increments each time that an iscommit() call is made. No one-to-one correspondence exists between this value and the number of explicit COMMIT WORK statements that are executed.

item.name: Compressions, s⁻¹
item.description: Increments each time that a data page is compressed.

item.name: Data read-aheads, s⁻¹
item.description: The count of data-path-only scans.

item.name: Deadlocks
item.description: Increments each time that a potential deadlock is detected and prevented.

item.name: ISAM delete, s⁻¹
item.description: ISAM. Increments when a row is deleted

item.name: Distributed deadlock time-outs
item.description: Increments each time that the distributed deadlock time-out value is exceeded while a user thread is waiting for a lock.

item.name: Buffer flushes, s⁻¹
item.description: The number of times that the buffer pool has been flushed to the disk.

item.name: Generic page allocations, s⁻¹
item.description: The number of generic page allocations.

item.name: Generic page cursors, s⁻¹
item.description: The number of cursors used against generic pages.

item.name: Generic page deletes, s⁻¹
item.description: The number of generic page deletes.

item.name: Generic pages freed, s⁻¹
item.description: The number of generic pages freed and returned to tblspaces.

item.name: Generic page reads, s⁻¹
item.description: The number of generic page reads.

item.name: Generic page updates, s⁻¹
item.description: The number of generic page updates.

item.name: Generic page writes, s⁻¹
item.description: The number of generic page writes.

item.name: Index read-aheads, s⁻¹
item.description: The count of read-aheads that traverse index leaves.

item.name: ISAM total, s⁻¹
item.description: ISAM. The total number of calls

item.name: Index-data read-aheads, s⁻¹
item.description: The count of read-aheads that go from index leaves to data pages.

item.name: Latch waits, s⁻¹
item.description: Stores the number of times that a thread was required to wait for a shared-memory latch. A large number of latch waits typically results from a high volume of processing activity in which the database server is logging most of the transactions.

item.name: Lock requests, s⁻¹
item.description: Increments each time that a lock is requested.

item.name: Log record read-aheads, s⁻¹
item.description: The log records that the database server read ahead.

item.name: Lock waits, s⁻¹
item.description: Increments each time that a user thread must wait for a lock.

item.name: Checkpoints
item.description: The number of checkpoints since the boot time.

item.name: ISAM open, s⁻¹
item.description: ISAM. Increments when a tblspace is opened

item.name: Overbuffers, s⁻¹
item.description: The number of times that the database server could not find a free shared-memory buffer.

item.name: Overlocks, s⁻¹
item.description: The number of times that the database server attempted to allocate locks more than 15 times.

item.name: Overuserthreads, s⁻¹
item.description: The number of times that a user attempted to exceed the maximum number of user threads.

item.name: Read-ahead pages used, s⁻¹
item.description: Indicates the number of pages used that the database server read ahead. If this number is significantly less than the total number of pages read ahead, the read-ahead parameters might be set too high.

item.name: ISAM read, s⁻¹
item.description: ISAM. Increments when the read function is called

item.name: ISAM rewrite, s⁻¹
item.description: Increments when an update occurs.

item.name: ISAM rollback, s⁻¹
item.description: ISAM. Increments when a transaction is rolled back.

item.name: Sequential scans, s⁻¹
item.description: Increments for each sequential scan.

item.name: ISAM start, s⁻¹
item.description: ISAM. Increments the pointer within an index

item.name: System CPU
item.description: The total system CPU time that all user threads use, expressed in seconds. This entry is updated every 15 seconds.

item.name: User CPU
item.description: The total user CPU time that all user threads use, expressed in seconds. This entry is updated every 15 seconds.

item.name: ISAM write, s⁻¹
item.description: ISAM. Increments with each write call

item.name: Current log position
item.description: The size of the physical log in pages.

item.name: Log pages written, s⁻¹
item.description: The number of pages written to the logical log.

item.name: Records written, s⁻¹
item.description: The number of records written to the logical log.

item.name: Log writes, s⁻¹
item.description: The number of writes to the logical log.

item.name: Phys pages written, s⁻¹
item.description: The number of pages written to the physical log.

item.name: Phys writes, s⁻¹
item.description: The number of writes to disk.

item.name: Phys pages per write
item.description: The number of pages written to the physical log.

item.name: Phys log size
item.description: The size of the physical log in pages.

item.name: Phys log used
item.description: The number of pages used in the log.

item.name: Phys log used %
item.description: The percent of pages used.

item.name: Threads on buffer
item.description: Threads waiting for a buffer.

item.name: Threads on checkpoint
item.description: Threads waiting for a checkpoint.

item.name: Threads on logbuffer
item.description: Threads waiting for a write of the logical-log buffer.

item.name: Threads on IO
item.description: Threads waiting for IO.

item.name: Threads on lock
item.description: Threads waiting for a lock.

item.name: Long spins, s⁻¹
item.description: The number of times a thread had to spin more than 10,000 times to acquire a latch on a resource.

item.name: Threads ready
item.description: Ready threads.

item.name: Threads running
item.description: Threads running sqlexec.

item.name: Threads on mutex
item.description: Threads waiting for a mutex.

item.name: Scheduled calls, s⁻¹
item.description: The total number of scheduled calls.

item.name: Sessions
item.description: The number of sessions.

item.name: Threads on transaction
item.description: Threads waiting for a transaction.

item.name: Thread switches, s⁻¹
item.description: The total number of switches from one thread to another.

item.name: Threads total
item.description: The total number of threads.

item.name: VPs
item.description: The total number of virtual processors.

item.name: Threads on rollback
item.description: Threads waiting for a rollback.

item.name: Threads on condition
item.description: Threads waiting for a condition.

item.name: Yields 0, s⁻¹
item.description: Statistics on thread yields (yields 0).

item.name: Yields forever, s⁻¹
item.description: Statistics on thread yields (yields forever).

item.name: Yields n, s⁻¹
item.description: Statistics on thread yields (yields n).
